  "texts": [
    "A number of constraints in (19) should be left as (hard) constraints.",
    "These include the constraints relating the proposed and previous weights, i.e., the first line of constraints in (19).",
    "When the portfolio is long-only, the constraint w ≥ 0 should be left as a hard constraint, and similarly for a constraint such as c ≥ 0, i.e., that we do not borrow cash.",
    "When a leverage limit is strict or imposed by a mandate, it should be left as a hard constraint; when it is imposed by the portfolio manager to improve performance, or more likely, to help her avoid poor outcomes, it can be softened.",
    "The other constraints in (19) are candidates for softening."
